Japanese watchmaker Seiko Corp. said Tuesday its  group pre-tax loss widened 91 percent from a year earlier to 6.5 billion yen  (63 million dollars) in the year to March and forecast another loss this year.
The company said consolidated sales also declined during the period,  falling more than 11 percent to 335 billion yen.
Seiko forecast a pre-tax loss of five billion yen for the current year  despite a rebound in global sales to 360 billion yen.
